abstract: Who’s telling the truth about Ukraine? There’s one way to find out.
snippet: Who’s telling the truth about Ukraine? There’s one way to find out.
lead_paragraph: It’s just possible that common sense and reality have a shot at prying open the doors to the Senate chamber after all. After Republican senators claimed that it was perfectly reasonable to put a United States president on trial without hearing from any witnesses, a few of them are showing signs of recognizing that the truth matters. Or, at least, that the American people believe it does.

Four weeks later, news of John Bolton’s book manuscript about his time as President Donald Trump’s national security adviser has exploded into public view, sending a jolt through the president’s impeachment trial.

headline_print_headline: News of Bolton Book Sends Jolt Through Impeachment Trial

abstract: Jane Raskin, one of the president’s lawyers, said that despite the purported importance of the president’s personal lawyer, House impeachment investigators did not subpoena him.
snippet: Jane Raskin, one of the president’s lawyers, said that despite the purported importance of the president’s personal lawyer, House impeachment investigators did not subpoena him.
lead_paragraph: For the first time for the defense, Jane Raskin, one of the president’s lawyers, focused on the role of Rudy W. Giuliani, the president’s personal lawyer. She called him a “colorful distraction,” pointing out that despite his purported importance in the controversy, House impeachment investigators did not subpoena him to testify.
headline_main: Rudy Giuliani is a ‘colorful distraction,’ lawyer argues.

abstract: Senator Tom Cotton, Republican of Arkansas, rubbed his eyes with his right hand and yawned.
snippet: Senator Tom Cotton, Republican of Arkansas, rubbed his eyes with his right hand and yawned.
lead_paragraph: The slow start to the trial had some senators inside the chamber visibly struggling to remain engaged with President Trump’s lawyers.
headline_main: Senators yawn and take notes as the defense team talks.

abstract: As the liberal Bernie Sanders tightens his grip in Iowa, more traditional Democrats remain split among his four leading competitors, or are unsure altogether of whom to support.
snippet: As the liberal Bernie Sanders tightens his grip in Iowa, more traditional Democrats remain split among his four leading competitors, or are unsure altogether of whom to support.
lead_paragraph: BETTENDORF, Iowa — As they streamed out of the ballroom following a Scott County fund-raising banquet Saturday night, one after the other Iowa Democrats admitted that they still had not decided whom to support just over a week before the state’s presidential caucuses.

abstract: A former top adviser said that world leaders are not satisfied with so-called pull-aside at another event, like a United Nations meeting, which is what Volodymyr Zelensky received.
snippet: A former top adviser said that world leaders are not satisfied with so-called pull-aside at another event, like a United Nations meeting, which is what Volodymyr Zelensky received.
lead_paragraph: President Trump’s defense team keeps asserting that Volodymyr Zelensky, Ukraine’s president, got the meeting he wanted with Mr. Trump.

headline_main: Trump’s lawyers say Ukraine’s leader got the meeting he wanted, even though he said he did not.

abstract: President Trump’s defense team has not addressed assertions from the former national security adviser that Mr. Trump tied military aid to politically motivated investigations.
snippet: President Trump’s defense team has not addressed assertions from the former national security adviser that Mr. Trump tied military aid to politically motivated investigations.
lead_paragraph: President Trump’s lawyers ignored revelations from John R. Bolton, the president’s former national security adviser, as they opened the second day of their impeachment defense, doubling down on their claim that Mr. Trump cared about getting more European support for Ukraine, not investigations of his Democratic rivals.
headline_main: 2 hours in, Bolton’s revelations have not come up.

abstract: Senator Mitt Romney, Republican of Utah, said it was “increasingly likely” that more members of his party would push to hear from John R. Bolton about President Trump’s dealings with Ukraine.
snippet: Senator Mitt Romney, Republican of Utah, said it was “increasingly likely” that more members of his party would push to hear from John R. Bolton about President Trump’s dealings with Ukraine.
